aboutSections.description: Another great curry classic. But it is one you don’t see on many restaurant menus today. If you love curry you will love this. Imagine: rich curry gravy with deep fried spiced potato cheese balls (kofta) — almost like croquettes. Delicious.

steps.description: Get pan very hot then add the ghee. It should start smoking intensely then add the onions and tomatoes, cashews, cardamom, cloves, cinnamon stick, and bay leaf, and fry until vegetables are very caramelized.
Add the garlic ginger paste, spice blend, and brown sugar. Fry for 2 minutes.
Puree the curry in a blender or use an immersion blender.
Mix all the ingredients together and form balls. Make sure the dough is fully incorporated

Deep fry the balls in oil or ghee (350F) until golden brown and set on cooling rack to dry. Do not put them in the curry
immediately. You don't want soggy balls!
Serve with gravy over fluffy basmati rice topped with some of the kofta. Great with naan as well!

ingredients.name: all the spice blend, but reserve 1 tsp for kofta
